<p>Bayesian inference derives the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Posterior_probability" title=3D"Posterior probability">posterior probabilit=
y</a> as a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Consequence_relation" c=
lass=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Consequence relation">consequence</a> of two =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antecedent_(logic)" title=3D"Antec=
edent (logic)">antecedents</a>: a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Prior_probability" title=3D"Prior probability">prior probability</a> and a =
"<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Likelihood_function" title=3D"Lik=
elihood function">likelihood function</a>" derived from a <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Statistical_model" title=3D"Statistical model">stat=
istical model</a> for the observed data. Bayesian inference computes the po=
sterior probability according to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/B=
ayes%27_theorem" title=3D"Bayes' theorem">Bayes' theorem</a>:
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle P(H\mid E)=3D{\frac {P(E\mid H)\cdot P(H)}{P(E)}},}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>P</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>H</mi>
        <mo>=E2=88=A3<!-- =E2=88=A3 --></mo>
        <mi>E</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mi>P</mi>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mi>E</mi>
              <mo>=E2=88=A3<!-- =E2=88=A3 --></mo>
              <mi>H</mi>
