  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/2d6fd27873a3124e53f11f54eccc0f12200139ba" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.671ex; width:30.541ex; height:6.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle P=
(H\mid E)=3D{\frac {P(E\mid H)\cdot P(H)}{P(E)}},}"></span>
</p><p>where
</p>
<ul><li><span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">H</span> =
stands for any <i>hypothesis</i> whose probability may be affected by <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Experimental_data" title=3D"Experimenta=
l data">data</a> (called <i>evidence</i> below). Often there are competing =
hypotheses, and the task is to determine which is the most probable.</li>
<li><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D=
"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><mat=
